{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17624703","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17624703"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:19:14+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:19:14+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16952"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16952","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16952"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.95,0.02,0,0.02,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9642"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68689"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9642","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9642"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16952"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54146"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"9850"},{"type":"tags","id":"9855"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22751"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22756"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68689","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/68689"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the function of the atrioventricular bundle (bundle of His)?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Conducts impulses from atrioventricular node to bundle branches","Delays impulse conduction between chambers","Generates spontaneous action potentials","Conducts impulses between the atria","Coordinates ventricular repolarisation"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eatrioventricular bundle conducts impulses from the atrioventricular node to the bundle branches\u003C/strong\u003E. It is composed of specialised conducting cells that allow rapid propagation of electrical signals from the atria to the ventricles. This structure represents the only normal electrical connection between the upper and lower chambers of the heart.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGenerates spontaneous action potentials\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the function of the sinoatrial node, not the atrioventricular bundle\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDelays impulse conduction between chambers\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the function of the atrioventricular node, not the bundle\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConducts impulses between the atria\u003C/strong\u003E - Internodal pathways conduct impulses within the atria\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECoordinates ventricular repolarisation\u003C/strong\u003E - This is not a specific function of any part of the conducting system\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe atrioventricular bundle divides into left and right bundle branches which further distribute the electrical impulse to the ventricular myocardium via the Purkinje fibre network.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The atrioventricular bundle (bundle of His) conducts electrical impulses from the atrioventricular node to the bundle branches.","The atrioventricular bundle is the only electrical connection between the atria and ventricles.","The atrioventricular bundle is composed of specialised conducting cells that allow rapid impulse propagation."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2n